# Bingtastic API

The Bingtastic service provides usable data for developers to roll their own
[Bing Rewards](http://go.microsoft.com/?linkid=9778718&rrid=_ad8ea4a6-b009-6b60-1c54-667a72de00e5) applications.

# Group Search Queries

## Default [/{bings}{minwords}{maxwords}{categories}{response}]
Returns assembled search queries with metadata. Defaults to 30 items, 2-4 words per phrase, all categories.

### Default [GET]

+ Parameters
    + bings (optional, number, `30`) ... number of nodes on the object to generate.
    + minwords (optional, number, `2`) ... minimum word count in any given phrase. _Minimum: 1_
    + maxwords (optional, number, `4`) ... maximum words count in any given phrase. _Must be greater than `minwords`_
    + categories (optional, comma-separated string, `images,videos`) ... generate prefixes only from categories provided. Reference `Metadata:Categories` for listing of valid options
    + response (optional, string, `jsonp`) ... format in which data will be provided. Reference `Metadata:Response Types

+ Response 200 (application/json)
    
        [{
            type: "default",
            query: "swear+actual",
            text: "swear actual",
            template: "http://www.bing.com/search?q={{query}}&go=&qs=n&form=&pq={{query}}&sc=0-0&sp=-1&sk=",
            url: "http://www.bing.com/search?q=swear+actual&go=&qs=n&form=&pq=swear+actual&sc=0-0&sp=-1&sk="
        },
        {
            type: "omnibar",
            query: "transaction+invisible",
            text: "transaction invisible",
            template: "http://www.bing.com/search?q={{query}}&setmkt=en-US",
            url: "http://www.bing.com/search?q=transaction+invisible&setmkt=en-US"
        }]

# Group Metadata

## Categories [/?request=categories]
Provides the list of available categories as an array.

### Categories [GET]
+ Response 200

        [
            "default",
            "omnibar",
            "images",
            "videos",
            "maps",
            "news"
        ]

